title: Crimson Tide land at No. 11 in the CFP rankings
description: Barring an upset in Saturday's ACC title game between Clemson and SMU, Alabama might be headed back to the College Football Playoff for the ninth time in the past 11 seasons, as the Crimson Tide were ranked No. 11 in the latest CFP rankings Tuesday.
author: Mark Schlabach

title: CFP Anger Index: Why Ole Miss and Miami should both be furious over Bama's ranking
description: The five teams that have the most to be upset about with the second to last CFP ranking.
author: David Hale

title: Smiling Van Nistelrooy brings belief back to Leicester
description: His Leicester side had to ride their luck at times against West Ham, but victory for a smiling Ruud van Nistelrooy is already giving Foxes fans their "belief" back.

title: Scotland's golden generation miss their golden hour
description: This Scotland squad often talk about what they deserve. But yet again they have not earned what they think they are due.

title: Azim fights former world champion on Sky Sports
description: Adam Azim will take on Sergey Lipinets at the OVO Arena Wembley on February 1, live on Sky Sports.

title: Broncos spoil career-night parties for Browns' Winston and Jeudy
description: Ja'Quan McMillian's game-clinching touchdown with less than two minutes remaining spoiled the career-night turns by Jameis Winston and Jerry Jeudy as Denver Broncos clinched a 41-32 shootout win over Cleveland Browns.

title: CFP penultimate ranks: 3-loss Alabama leaps 2-loss Miami
description: The Tide moved ahead of the Canes on Tuesday to grab the inside track to the final playoff spot. Oregon, Texas, Penn State and Notre Dame make up the top 4.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Pritchard drops great quote about chirping Heat's Erik Spoelstra
description: Payton Pritchard had some choice words for Erik Spoelstra and the Heat while giving them 25 points in the Celtics' blowout win Monday.
